# Handling Missing Information

When key details are missing, follow this approach.

## Process

1. **Say so clearly**: "To make this accurate, I need: …"
2. **Ask minimum necessary** (2–5 questions only)
3. **Use `[TBD: …]`** for unknowns instead of guessing
4. **Never hallucinate** specific tools, APIs, or requirements

## Default Action

If user doesn't provide more info, **generate high-quality template with `[TBD]` markers** instead of refusing.

## Examples

✅ Good: "The API endpoint is `[TBD: provide endpoint URL]`"
❌ Bad: "The API endpoint is `https://api.example.com/v1/users`" (when unknown)

✅ Good: "Authentication uses `[TBD: OAuth2 / JWT / API key]`"
❌ Bad: "Authentication uses OAuth2" (when not specified)
